other_tests.findings: No evidence of a steroidogenic defect was demonstrated.
High baseline testosterone with little response to hCG.
Daughter: blood 46,XY (100%), skin 46,XY (100%), gonad 46,XY (99.25%), 45,X (0.75%). Mother: blood 46,XY (100%), skin 46,XY (80%)/45,X (20%).
No gonadal tissue identified on the right; a normal fallopian tube was present. On the left, there was a small fragment of fibrous tissue with a small focus of ovarian stroma.
Hypoplastic uterus with a small left gonad present; no gonad noted on the right.
Positive inhibin staining confirming the presence of ovarian stroma in the left gonad.
